      "span_text": "For the Wrist Lock, there is no entire row of zeros in the J matrix (Equation (8)). [CITATION_1] This means that it is still possible to rotate around the X-axis of Frame{4} in wrist singularity, but it is produced by the first three joints, which would also change the position of the end effector (i.e. not possible in 6 DOF).",
